	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I've seen similar graphics in a Game Boy color racing game. How does that work exactly? Is it essentially a software version of Cosmic Epsilon, where each texture row at each scale is stored in the cartridge?</div><br />Each <span class="posthilit">line</span> is stored at different widths VRAM (generated at runtime I suppose) and they are then scrolled in by midframe scroll adjusts.<br />EDIT: all pre-rendered/drawn, no runtime stuff happens.. the small stuff looks too good.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


